69
00:04:16.399 --> 00:04:20.221
So as an entry point to the discussion of the microbiome in CAR T cell

70
00:04:20.280 --> 00:04:21.719
therapy, I'll start there.

71
00:04:22.540 --> 00:04:25.880
I do want to highlight that these insights in terms of the

72
00:04:25.900 --> 00:04:27.780
microbiome are

73
00:04:28.860 --> 00:04:32.810
based on or really have a strong foundation in other studies of

74
00:04:32.840 --> 00:04:36.300
the microbiome, not only immune checkpoint blockade, but also

75
00:04:36.400 --> 00:04:38.180
allogeneic transplant research.

76
00:04:38.980 --> 00:04:42.800
As Rob alluded to, there's a really large amount of

77
00:04:42.860 --> 00:04:46.690
data with over a decade of literature supporting

78
00:04:46.780 --> 00:04:50.700
that the intestinal microbiome impacts graft versus host disease outcomes

79
00:04:50.720 --> 00:04:54.600
in the allo transplant space and also increases antibiotic resistance.

80
00:04:54.910 --> 00:04:58.469
And I'm going to talk to you about the insights in terms of how antibiotic

81
00:04:58.520 --> 00:05:02.180
exposures prior to CAR T cell therapy are associated with decreased

82
00:05:02.280 --> 00:05:05.330
progression-free survival, decreased overall survival, and

83
00:05:05.340 --> 00:05:07.340
increased neurotoxicity.

84
00:05:09.240 --> 00:05:13.160
So here are the CAR T cell therapies that have been FDA approved

85
00:05:13.880 --> 00:05:17.020
targeting both CD19 and BCMA targets.

86
00:05:17.780 --> 00:05:21.680
What we know is that these therapies have led to

87
00:05:21.820 --> 00:05:25.680
really notable advances in clinical outcomes for patients

88
00:05:26.060 --> 00:05:29.920
with relapse refractory B cell malignancies and multiple myeloma.

89
00:05:30.600 --> 00:05:34.220
However, patients still either don't respond or might have

90
00:05:34.320 --> 00:05:38.140
limited duration of remission, and this is one of the factors that led

91
00:05:38.220 --> 00:05:42.120
