00:10:15.180 --> 00:10:18.120
low risk antibiotics, and high risk antibiotics.

167
00:10:18.180 --> 00:10:21.320
And here you can see this yellow line.

168
00:10:21.400 --> 00:10:24.680
Again, they saw that patients exposed to high risk antibiotics, as noted here,

169
00:10:25.060 --> 00:10:28.840
piperacillin-tazobactam, meropenem, ceftazidime, and cefepime,

170
00:10:28.960 --> 00:10:31.939
had the lowest proportion of surviving.

171
00:10:32.020 --> 00:10:35.880
A subsequent study also delved into, in a multicenter

172
00:10:35.960 --> 00:10:39.820
cohort, no or low risk antibiotics, cephalosporins, and PIM.

173
00:10:40.240 --> 00:10:43.000
And again, PIM still had the worst

174
00:10:43.740 --> 00:10:44.870
progression-free survival.

175
00:10:47.700 --> 00:10:51.140
And then finally, this study broadened PIM.

176
00:10:51.260 --> 00:10:55.140
So PIM was a subset of antibiotics that we were looking at

177
00:10:55.500 --> 00:10:59.440
that target obligate anaerobes. And here in this study, they broadened

